<td width="100%">
<font size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Betaroot</font><font size="2"> - 08-05-2003 01:05</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">A few minutes ago, Scott Hartsman, SoE Technical Director and goatee-faced albino (probably), broadcast across all EverQuest servers that the highly anticipated (no, really) cave-centric crawlfest Lost Dungeons of Norrath is now accepting Beta applications from lowly cash mines (customers).<br><br>Is this a genuine attempt to gain fresh expertise beyond the normal Beta test clique  people-who-arent-Furor  or a cynically mislabelled demo designed to drum up interest in Orcs?  And Frogloks.  Again.<br><br>Please, decide for me.  Its 7 am and I havent slept yet.<br><br><a href="http://everquest.station.sony.com/lostdungeons/beta/register.jsp" target="_top">LDoN Beta Registration</a><br><br><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=6538" target="_top">Discuss</a></font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">- <a href="mailto:edano@magecompendium.com">Edano</a></font><br><br></td>
</tr>
